  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Arif Md. Yeasin Jwadder versus State of Assam and Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_5_881_905','2025INSC785'); ><font size='4'> <strong>ARIF MD. YEASIN JWADDER<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF ASSAM AND ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 881</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 785</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004362025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SURYA KANT<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, N KOTISWAR SINGH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The instant matter arises from a series of encounters reported in the State of Assam (Respondent No. 1), the authenticity of which has been called into question on various counts. The appellant asserted that no meaningful or effective inquiry has been undertaken in respect the guidelines laid down in People&rsquo;s Union for Civil Liberties &amp; Anr. v. State of Maharashtra &amp; Ors. has been flouted blatantly. Headnotes&dagger; Public Interest Litigation &ndash; Fake Police Encounters &ndash; Directions by the Supreme Court &ndash; Whether the allegations made<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 28-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2867/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_5_881_905','2025INSC785','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div c